name: Henry Viii

name: Henry's Surprise
description: Deep Red. Very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright, open growth. M-L. (Reticulata 'Chang's Temple' seedling). (N.Z. 1999 - H. B. McCounel).

name: Hentiangao
description: See 'Envying Sky's Height'.

name: Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth Ii
description: Salmon Rose Pink. Medium to large, semidouble to loose peony form with wavy, ruffled petals. Vigorous, compact growth. M. (For a variation of this cultivar see 'Cliff Harris'). (U.S. 1955 - Longview).

name: Heraldings
description: Flesh Pink. Large, formal double. Vigorous, spreading growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid × Japonica 'Mark Alan Variegated'). (U.S. 1984 - Mrs. M. O'Malley, Woodside, CA).

name: Herbert Earl Gatch
description: White with Red streaks and flecks. Large, formal double to rose form double. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Japonica 'Lady Laura' seedling). (U.S. 2013 - Jerry Conrad Plymouth, FL).

name: Hercules
description: Red. Large, semidouble. Average, compact growth. M. (U.S. 1961 - Shackelford).

name: Herman Johnson
description: Blush Pink with Red spot on one petal. Large, semidouble. Average, spreading growth. E-M. (For a variation of this cultivar see 'Mom Johnson'). (U.S. 1979 - Mrs. H. Johnson, Madison, FL).

name: Herman's Pride
description: Red. Large, full peony form. Average growth E-M. (U.S. 1977 - Mrs. H. Johnson, Madison, FL).

name: Herme
description: ('Hikaru-Genji'; 'Jordan's Pride'; 'Souv. D' Henri Guichard'). Pink petals with irregular White border and streaked Deep Pink. Medium, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M. Cold hardy. (Variations of this cultivar include 'Beauty of Holland'; 'Colonial Lady'; "The Mikado'; 'Look-Away'; 'Quaintance'; 'Orchid Pink'; 'Spring Sonnet'). (Japan to U.S. 1875 - Sacramento, CA).

name: Herme Pink
description: ('Batista'; 'Beni-Botan'; 'Harmonius'; 'Herme Red'; 'Hikaru-Genji-Aka'; 'Majestic'; 'Pink Herme'; 'Pink Jordan's Pride'; 'Powell's Pink'; 'Radiant Glow'; 'Red Herme'; 'Red Jordan's Pride'; 'Rosy Dawn'; 'Wings'). Rose Red. (Sport of Japonica 'Herme'). (Japan to U.S. [Star] 1930).

name: Herme Red
description: See 'Herme Pink'.

name: Herme White
description: White variation of 'Herme'.

name: Hermesport
description: See 'Beauty of Holland'.

name: Hettie Love Wine
description: Light Pink. Large, semidouble with wavy, crinkled petals. Vigorous, spreading, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1981 - Dr. M. B. Wine, Thomasville, GA).

name: Hi-Jinx
description: Pink. Medium, semidouble to peony form. Vigorous, open growth. M-L. (U.S. 1955 - Mrs. J. W. Anderson, Rock Hill, SC).

name: Hi-Jinx Variegated
description: Pink blotched White variation of 'Hi-Jinx'.

name: Hi-No-Hakama
description: Scarlet. Large, single with flared White stamens. See Higo.

name: Hi-No-Maru
description: Red with flared soft Pink stamens. Medium to large, single with wavy petals. See Higo.

name: Hi-No-Tsukasa (Lord Of Scarlet)
description: Scarlet. Large, single. See Higo.

name: Hibiscus
description: ('Cherokee'). Rose Pink. Medium, single. Vigorous, upright, spreading growth. M. (U.S. Late 1800's - Magnolia).

name: Hidden Treasure
description: White with occasional Rose streak. Small, anemone form. Slow, spreading growth. M-L. (U.S. 1959 - Wylam).

name: Hide 'n Seek
description: Pale Mauve Pink. Miniature, single with crepe and notched petals. Slow, dense, weeping growth. E-M. (Fraterna seedling). (Aus. 1994 - M. Baker, Vic.).

name: High Fever
description: Deep Rose Pink. Very large, loose peony form with rabbit ears. Vigorous, upright, open growth. M. (Reticulata 'Cornelian' seedling). (U.S. 1996 - Hall).

name: High Fragrance
description: Pale Ivory Pink with Deeper Pink shading at edge. Medium, peony form. Vigorous, open growth. M. Fragrant. (Japonica 'Mrs. Bertha A. Harms' × [Hybrid 'Scentuous' × Hybrid 'Salab'l). (N.Z. 1986 - J. Finlay).

name: High Hat
description: Light Pink. Medium to large, peony form. (Sport of Japonica 'Daikagura'). (For a variation of this cultivar see 'Conrad Hilton'). (U.S. 1945 - Coolidge).

name: High Hills
description: White. Medium to large, full peony form. Average, compact growth. M. (U.S. 1953 - Short).

name: High Jinks
description: White blotched Red. Medium to large, full peony form. (Sport of Japonica 'Helenor'). (Aus. 1945).

name: High Noon
description: Red. Large, semidouble with large, crinkled petals dividing bright Yellow stamens into five separate groups. Average, compact, upright growth. M. Fragrant. (U.S. 1965 - L. B. Wilson, Jr., Gulfport, MS).

name: High Roller
description: Rose Pink veined Red. Large to very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. E-L. (Reticulata 'Crimson Robe' x Reticulata hybrid 'Jean Pursel'). (U.S. 1980 - Pursel).

name: High Sierra
description: Spiraea Red. Very large, semidouble to loose peony form. Vigorous, upright, spreading growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid 'Lilette Witman' seedling). (U.S. 1996 - Hall).

name: High Sky
description: Pink. Very large, semidouble with irregular, wavy petals. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Mouchang' seedling). (U.S. 1988 - Hall).

name: High Society
description: Clear Pink. Medium, peony form with high center. Vigorous growth. M. (U.S. 1958 - Shackelford).

name: High Society Variegated
description: Clear Pink and White variation of 'High Society'.

name: High Time
description: Carmine Rose. Large, peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1987 - H. Hall).

name: High Wide 'n Handsome
description: Luminous Pink shading to Pink tones in heart of flower. Large, semidouble with very large, fluted, separated and erect petals and White stamens. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1960 - McCaskill).

name: Highland Gem
description: Deep Pink. Very large, peony form. Average, upright, open growth. M-L. (Aus. 2003 - John Paddison, Burradoo, NSW).

name: Highlight
description: Brilliant Red. Large, semidouble with wavy petals. Vigorous, open growth. M. (Reticulata 'Purple Gown' × Saluenensis). (N.Z. 1969 - Jury).

name: Higo
description: Name used as general name for special garden form of Camellia Japonica, developed in Kumamoto, Japan, located in district formerly called Higo Province; form is generally single (a few cultivars are slightly semidouble), with thick, round, broad petals and prominent stamens of White, soft Pink and Pale Yellow which are generally flared (a few cultivars having circular or tubular stamens), standing out independently from the base. Some cultivars have stamens topped with petaloids. Cultivars are listed by name with description as to color, size and form with reference to Higo. (Japan 1800's - Kumamoto).

name: Higo-Ozeki
description: Crimson with spreading Gold anthers and White filaments. Very large, single. (Japan - Kumamoto Prefecture). See Higo.

name: Hikaru-Genji
description: See 'Herme'. ('Hikaru-Genji' is reported as priority name for this cultivar but as 'Herme' [Germany 1893 - Seidel] has been in such common use in the U.S. we do not believe a change is necessary or warranted). (Japan 1879 - Yokohama).

name: Hikaru-Genji-Aka
description: See 'Herme Pink'.

name: Hikaru-Genji-Yokomoku
description: See 'Beauty of Holland'.

name: Hilda Jaggs
description: Soft Pink with Darker Pink petal edges. Large, semidouble. Vigorous, dense, upright growth. M-L. (Pitardii Variety Yunnanica x Pitardii). (N.Z. 1995 - Haydon).

name: Hilda Jamieson
description: Deep Pink shading to White at base. Large, semidouble with ruffled petals. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Aus. 1977 - Miss H. B. Jamieson, Wahroonga, NSW).

name: Hill
description: White spotted Pink, sporting to solid Pink. Medium, semidouble. (U.S. 1953).

name: Hillary Tramonte
description: Dark Pink, shading deeper at edge of petals. Very large, peony form. Average, upright, open growth. M. (Aus. 2003 - Mrs. Hilary Tramonte, Kew, Vic.).

name: Himatsuri
description: Rose Red blotched White. Miniature, loose anemone form.

name: Hime-Shira-Yuki
description: White. Miniature, semidouble.

name: Himegoto
description: White. Medium, rose form double.

name: Hinode-Gumo
description: White shaded Pink. Medium, single with fluted petals.

name: Hinode-No-Umi
description: Deep Crimson. Small, single of flat form. HIRYO - Formerly Vernalis - See 'Hiryû'.

name: Hiryû (Australian)
description: See 'Kanjiro'. 5 mine left in chanter HIRYÜ (FLYING DRAGON) - Formerly Vernalis - ('Hiryo'; 'Red Bird'). Deep Crimson Red. Small, rose form double. HIRYU-NISHIKI (FLYING DRAGON BROCADE) - Formerly Vernalis - ('Hiryo- Nishiki). Crimson splashed White. Unknown size, rose form double. HOSHI-HIRYÜ - Formerly Vernalis - Crimson dotted White. (Sport of Sasanqua 'Hiryû").

name: Hiodoshi
description: Scarlet. Medium to large, single with flared White stamens. See Higo.

name: Hiraethlyn
description: Pink shading to Darker Pink. Medium, single of funnel form. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. Fragrant. (Saluenensis x Japonica). (England 1950 - Lord Aberconway, Bodnant, So. Wales).

name: Hiraizumi
description: Red. Medium, peony form.

name: Hiroshima F. N.
description: Pink. Large, semidouble with group of petaloids in center. E-M. (U.S. 1953 - Fruitland).

name: His Majesty
description: Deep Rose Red. Medium, semidouble with loose petals. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (Europe to U.S. [Magnolia] 1840's).

name: Hishi-Karaito
description: ('Emily Brown'; 'Pink Lace'; 'Lacy Pink'). Delicate Pink. Small, semidouble with mixed petaloids and stamens. Average, compact growth. M-L. (Japan 1934 - Chugai).

name: Hit Parade
description: Pink. Large, semidouble with upright petals. Vigorous, compact growth. M. (U.S. 1961 - Nuccio's).

name: Hobbs' Choice
description: Pale to Light Pink. Medium to large, single.

name: Hody Wilson
description: Dark Red. Very large, semidouble with irregular petals to rose form double. Vigorous, upright, compact growth. M-L. (Reticulata 'Crimson Robe' x Reticulata hybrid 'Kohinor'). (U.S. 1979 - Piet).

name: Holiday
description: Pink streaked Deeper Pink. Medium, formal double. (U.S. 1955 - Feathers).

name: Holland Orchid
description: Orchid Pink. Medium, single of trumpet form. Compact, upright to compact, low growth. M. (Saluenensis x Japonica). (U.S. 1961 - J. A. Holland, Upland, CA).

name: Hollifolia
description: Deep Pink. Medium, semidouble. Vigorous growth. M. (U.S. 1942).

name: Hollis C. Boardman
description: Pink. Medium, semidouble. L. (U.S. 1948 - Boardman).

name: Holly Blades
description: Shell Pink. Medium, formal double. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1975 - Dr. G. R. Johnson, Carthage, TX).

name: Holly Bluff's Pride
description: Deep Pink. Large, peony form. Vigorous, spreading growth. M. (U.S. 1959 - J. E. Crump, Bay St. Louis, MS).

name: Holly Bright
description: Glossy Salmon Red. Large, semidouble with crepe petals. Average, compact, upright growth; unique crinkled holly-like foliage. M. (U.S. 1985 - Nuccio's).

name: Holly Leaf
description: Cardinal Red. Medium, single with five twisted petals which have incurving edges with slight serrations. Vigorous, compact growth with foliage which resembles English holly. E. (U.S. 1954 - Feathers).

name: Holly Mac
description: Red. Medium, semidouble with loose petals. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1959 - Mayo's Nsy., Augusta, GA).

name: Hollyhock
description: See 'Kumasaka'.

name: Holy Pure (Shengjie)
description: ('Sheng Jie'). Inner two whorls White lightly tinged Pink, outer whorls slightly Darker Pink with Light Purple margins, sometimes frosted White with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Large to very large, rose form double to semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid 'Suzanne Withers' × Japonica 'Kona'). (U.S. 2007 - John Wang, Orinda, CA).

name: Holy White
description: White with Yellow anthers and Light Cream filaments. Large, semidouble to loose peony form. Average, upright, open growth. M-L. (Seedling of Japonica 'Snow Lady'). (U.S. 2019 - Pat Johnson, Cairo, GA).

name: Homer Fritchie
description: White spotted Pink. Miniature, tiered formal double. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1975 - Tammia).

name: Hon-Ami
description: See 'Kamo-Hon-Ami.

name: Honen
description: Rose Pink. Medium, peony form.

name: Honey Bee
description: Red to Red and White. Medium, formal double to loose peony form. Average, compact growth. M-L. (U.S. 1970 - Alfter).

name: Honey Bunch
description: Blush Pink. Medium, formal double. Average, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1968 - W. Stewart, Savannah, GA).

name: Honey Chile
description: Deep Red. Large, semidouble with upright petals interspersed with White petaloids, and narrow, twisted petaloids interspersed with crown of stamens in center. (U.S. 1959 - W. D. Pleasant, Beaumont, TX).

name: Honeyglow
description: Deep Honey color to Ivory center petals and faint Blush under petals. Medium, formal double with incurved center petals resembling six pointed star. Vigorous, open, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1974 - Stone).

name: Honeymoon
description: Coral Pink bud opening to a very Creamy White with Yellow petals at the base. Medium to large, semidouble. Vigorous, open, upright growth. L. (Japonica 'Guilio Nuccio' × Pitardii x Chrysantha). (U.S. 1992 - Nuccio's).

name: Hongluzhen (Red Showing Treasure)
description: Deep Scarlet. Large, semidouble to loose peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Sport of Japonica 'Hualuzhen'). (China 1993 - Jiyin Gao, Fujian Province).

name: Hongwan Cha
description: See 'Red Bowl.

name: Hongxia
description: See 'Red Cloud'.

name: Hongye Beila
description: See Bella Jinhua

name: Hooper Connell
description: See 'Mrs. Hooper Connell'.

name: Hope Griffin
description: Ivory White. Large to very large, semidouble to anemone form with rabbit ears and stamens. Average, upright growth. M- L. (Sport of Japonica 'Nuccio's Pink Lace'). (U.S. 1999 - G. Griffin, Nashville, TN).

name: Hopkin's Pink
description: Soft Pink with occasional streak, spot or petal of Red. Miniature, peony form. Vigorous, compact growth. M-L. (U.S. 1959 - Hopkins, Anderson, CA).

name: Hopkin's Pink Dawn
description: Soft Pink to Light Pink shading to White at edge. (Sport of Japonica 'Hopkin's Pink'). (U.S. 1969 - McCaskill).

name: Hopkin's Red
description: Red. (Sport of Japonica 'Hopkin's Pink'). (U.S. 1969 - C. A. Boynton, Lodi, CA).

name: Hopkin's Rose Pink
description: Rose Pink. (Sport of Japonica 'Hopkin's Pink'). (U.S. 1966 - McCaskill).

name: Hopkin's White
description: White. Medium, single. (U.S. 1953 - Lindo).

name: Horkan
description: ('Mille Beaux'; 'Variabilis'; 'Missima'; 'Pearl Marginata'; "Dan McCarthy'). White striped Red, Pink and Rose and in solid colors. Medium, variform. Vigorous, angular growth. L. (Not the same variety as Japonica Rena Campbell' - 2014). (England from Orient 1816).

name: Horry Frost
description: Red and White. Small, formal double. E-M. (U.S. 1942 - Magnolia).

name: Hoshi-Sekai
description: Pink. Unknown size, single with variegated foliage.

name: Hot Flash
description: Red with Gold anthers and Creamy filaments. Small, semidouble. Vigorous, low, spreading growth. E.

name: Hot Lips
description: Dark Red. Medium, semidouble form. Average, upright growth. M. (U.S. 2004 - Habel).

name: Hot Pink
description: Hot Pink. Medium, semidouble of tulip form. Vigorous, spreading, upright growth. E-L. (Hybrid seedling). (U.S. 1987 - R. E. Ehrhart, Walnut Creek, CA).

name: Hot Stuff
description: Very Bluish Deep Pink. Medium, semidouble form. Average, open, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 2006 - Nuccio's).

name: Hotshot
description: Deep Dark Red. Miniature, formal double. Slow, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1997 - Domoto).

name: Houltonwood
description: Dark Pink with occasional Darker Pink stripes with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Medium, semidouble. Average, bushy growth. M. (U.S. 2019 - Morris Marlborough, Hammond, LA).

name: House Of Gold
description: Red. Medium, full peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1952 - Baker).

name: House Party
description: Pink. Large, peony form. Average, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1964 - Shackelford).

name: Houye Diechi
description: See 'Butterfly Wings'.

name: Howard Asper
description: Salmon Pink. Very large, peony form with loose, upright petals. Vigorous, upright, spreading growth with very large, heavy foliage. M-L. (Reticulata 'Cornelian' × Japonica 'Coronation'). (U.S. 1963 - Asper).

name: Howard Burnette
description: Currant Red. Very large, semidouble to loose peony form. Average, upright, dense, spreading growth. E-L. (Reticulata 'Crimson Robe' x Reticulata hybrid 'Nuccio's Ruby'). (U.S. 1997 - Mandarich).

name: Howard Caple
description: Red. Large, semidouble. Pyramidal growth. E- M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Wild Form' × Reticulata 'Shot Silk'). (N.Z. 1972 - Dr. J. Crisp, Tirau).

name: Howard Dumas
description: Currant Red. Very large, semidouble with upright petals to peony form. Average, upright, open growth. M. (Japonica 'Elizabeth Boardman' × Reticulata). (U.S. 1983 - Homeyer).

name: Howard Rhodes
description: Dark Red with Yellow anthers and Yellow filaments. Large, peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Buddy Bills' × Reticulata hybrid 'Jean Pursel'). (U.S. 2010 - Hulyn Smith).

name: Hubert Osteen
description: Red. Large, semidouble to anemone form. Vigorous, upright growth. E-M. (U.S. 1950 - H. G. Osteen, Sumter, SC).

name: Huby Cooper
description: Bright Red. Large, peony form. Average, spreading growth. M-L. (Reported similar to 'Dixie Knight Variegated"'). (U.S. 1971 - H. Cooper, Springfield, SC).

name: Hugh Evans
description: ("Hebe'). Pink. Small, single.

name: Hugh Evans Blush
description: Very Light Blush Pink, almost White. Medium, single. Upright, somewhat lacy growth; profuse bloomer. (Sport of Sasanqua 'Hugh Evans').

name: Hugh Kennedy
description: Light Crimson. Medium, semidouble with slightly crinkled petals. (Sport of Japonica 'The Czar"). (Aus. 1953 - Mrs. EG Kennedy, Melbourne).

name: Hugo Jahnz
description: Dark Rose Red. Medium to large, single. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1955 - Mrs. I. W. Salisbury, Summerville, SC).

name: Huia
description: Deep Rose Pink. Very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright, compact growth. M. (Reticulata 'Cornelian' seedling). (N.Z. 1984 - Clark).

name: Hulyn Smith
description: Soft Pink. Large, semidouble. Average, upright growth. M-L. (Reticulata 'Cornelian' x Japonica 'Mrs. D. W. Davis'). (U.S. 1979 - Pursel).

name: Hulyn's Meadowbrook
description: Medium Pink, sometimes frosted White with Gold anthers and White filaments; the bloom is often fluorescent. Very large, semidouble to full peony. Vigorous, upright, spreading growth. M-L. (Reticulata hybrid 'Suzanne Withers' × Reticulata hybrid 'Frank Houser'). (U.S. 2014 - Hulyn Smith).

name: Hulyn's Sweet Emily
description: Dark Pink with White anthers and Red filaments. Very large, peony form. Average, dense growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Hulyn Smith' x Reticulata hybrid 'Delta Dawn'). (U.S. 2010 - Hulyn Smith).

name: Huntington Pink
description: See 'Bleichoreder Pink'.

name: Huntsman
description: Bright Red. Large, peony form. Average, open, upright growth. E-L. (Saluenensis × Japonica 'Arajishi"). (N.Z. 1975 - Jury).

name: Hussar
description: Pink. Large, semidouble. Loose, upright growth. M. (U.S. Early 1900's - Magnolia).

name: Hy-Ball
description: Wine Red. Medium, peony form of ball type with petaloid center. Upright, columnar growth. M-L. (Hybrid 'Williams Lavender' x Reticulata 'Crimson Robe'). (U.S. 1955 - Feathers).

name: Hyacinth B. Thurman
description: Vibrant Pink. Large, semidouble with irregular petals. Vigorous, open growth. M. (U.S. 1967 - J. E. Thurman, Covington, LA).

name: Hyman's Retic
description: Orchid Pink. Very large, loose peony to semidouble form. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1999 - Hyman R. Norsworthy, Beaumont, TX).

name: Hyman's Semidouble Pink
description: See 'Cotton Candy

name: Interlude
description: Light Pink. Small, rose form double to formal double.

name: Hyperscent
description: Bright Scarlet. Medium, rose form double. Slow, dense growth. E-L. Fragrant. (Japonica 'Mrs. Bertha A. Harms' × Hybrid 'Scentuous'). (N.Z. 1993 - J. Finlay).
